      "content": "It is absolutely normal to want the pain to stop, and the way you're describing it is a very real response to a profound loss. Those platitudes from others are often meaningless when you're drowning in this kind of emptiness. If the constant, crushing feeling is what you're experiencing, it's a sign that you need a different kind of support than what friends can offer. Please consider talking to a mental health professional who can help you navigate this specific, unbearable weight.",
      "source": "target",
